column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

Specialty butchers and restocker orders put a good floor to prices as agents offered 220 liveweight and open auction cattle. Some well finished older steers along with some ideal younger cattle sold to stronger enquiry. Cows sold generally firm for type and condition.

Vealer steers sold from 250c to 356c as heifers ranged from 228c to 318c/kg. Yearling steers sold from 164c to 328c with heifers fetching 174c to 282c/kg.

Grown steers sold from 200c to 304c with heifers selling to 310c/kg. Light cows sold to 100c, medium cows sold from 72c to 230c with heavy cows fetching 240c to 250c/kg. Bulls sold from 150c to 250c/kg.

Market report: John Traeger.
